{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/what-the-heck-is-an-iife","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"f1f5dfca-f733-5ac9-8170-3ee10ad56757","html":"<p>Since the useEffect hook in React doesn’t allow the passed in function to be asynchronous, I found myself writing a lot of code blocks that look like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">useEffect</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">fetchData</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> response <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> <span class=\"token function\">apiCall</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setData</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>response<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token function\">fetchData</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I always thought there should be a better way to write this, but I never really cared enough to look into it.</p>\n<h3 id=\"so-are-you-going-to-tell-me-what-it-is\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#so-are-you-going-to-tell-me-what-it-is\" aria-label=\"so are you going to tell me what it is permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>So are you going to tell me what it is</h3>\n<p>An Immediately Invoked Function Expression (IIFE) is a function that runs when it’s defined and cannot be called again.</p>\n<p>It should be an <em>anonymous</em> function since there’s really no point in naming it.</p>\n<p><strong>The syntax</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// your function</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><em>Only showing arrow notation because it’s just objectively way more superior.</em></p>\n<p><strong>For example</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token function\">useEffect</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> response <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> <span class=\"token function\">apiCall</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setData</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>response<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"ok-thats-cool-but-so-what\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ok-thats-cool-but-so-what\" aria-label=\"ok thats cool but so what permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Ok that’s cool but so what</h3>\n<p>Honestly, IIFEs don’t have much use outside of making your code a little less ugly.</p>\n<p>But… you can also use IIFEs to:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Protect your functions</strong></p>\n<p>Because of scope, functions protect the variables inside of it. To protect the function, use an IIFE. It’s kind of like giving public access to the function with limited use.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Avoid ‘polluting the global namespace’</strong></p>\n<p>If you have a function that you know will only run once, why store it and waste space? Save trees. Use an IIFE.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/what-the-heck-is-an-iife","tagSlugs":["/tag/coding/","/tag/java-script/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-06-27T20:34:25.656Z","description":"I overheard a coworker mention something called an 'iffy' during a meeting. Now I've come to the conclusion that immediately invoked function expressions (IIFEs) are pretty useful in JavaScript.","tags":["Coding","JavaScript"],"title":"What the heck is an IIFE?","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/0b3c39e33318e58a05357f123ad927a4/photo.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/what-the-heck-is-an-iife"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}